# nettest

[![PyPI version](https://badge.fury.io/py/nettest.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/py/nettest)
[![CI](https://github.com/manumanohar11/nettest/actions/workflows/ci.yml/badge.svg)](https://github.com/manumanohar11/nettest/actions/workflows/ci.yml)
[![Python 3.9+](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.9+-blue.svg)](https://www.python.org/downloads/)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)

**Comprehensive network testing and diagnostics tool** for speed tests, latency analysis, route tracing, DNS resolution, TCP/HTTP connectivity, bufferbloat detection, VoIP quality scoring, and video conferencing service testing.

## Installation

```bash
pip install nettest
```

For all features:

```bash
pip install nettest[full]
```

## Quick Start

```bash
# Run a quick network test
nettest --profile quick

# Full comprehensive test
nettest --profile full

# Test video conferencing services (Teams, Zoom, Meet, etc.)
nettest --video-services

# Generate HTML report
nettest --format html --output report.html

# Interactive mode
nettest --interactive

# Live monitoring dashboard
nettest --monitor
```

## Features

- **Speed Testing** - Download/upload speeds via speedtest-cli
- **Latency Analysis** - Ping tests with jitter and packet loss statistics
- **Route Tracing** - MTR-based path analysis with hop-by-hop latency
- **DNS Resolution** - Timing analysis for DNS queries
- **TCP/HTTP Checks** - Port connectivity and HTTP endpoint testing
- **Bufferbloat Detection** - Queue-induced latency measurement
- **VoIP Quality** - MOS score calculation for voice quality
- **Video Services** - Test connectivity to Teams, Zoom, Meet, Webex, WhatsApp
- **Multiple Output Formats** - Terminal, HTML, JSON, Prometheus metrics, CSV

## Output Formats

```bash
# Rich terminal output (default)
nettest

# JSON for automation
nettest --format json

# HTML report with charts
nettest --format html --output report.html

# Prometheus metrics endpoint
nettest --prometheus-port 9101

# CSV export
nettest --export-csv results.csv
```

## Configuration

Create `nettest.yml` in your current directory or `~/.config/nettest/config.yml`:

```yaml
targets:
  - 8.8.8.8
  - 1.1.1.1
  - google.com

thresholds:
  latency:
    good: 50
    warning: 100
  jitter:
    good: 10
    warning: 30

profiles:
  quick:
    ping_count: 5
    skip_speedtest: true
  full:
    ping_count: 20
    video_services: true
    bufferbloat: true
```

Run the configuration wizard for guided setup:

```bash
nettest --wizard
```

## Profiles

| Profile | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `quick` | Fast ping-only test (~10 seconds) |
| `standard` | Balanced test with speedtest (~1 minute) |
| `full` | All tests enabled (~3-5 minutes) |
| `gaming` | Optimized for gaming latency requirements |
| `voip` | VoIP quality focused testing |
| `streaming` | Streaming-optimized thresholds |

```bash
nettest --profile gaming
```

## System Requirements

### Required
- Python 3.9+
- `ping` command (standard on all systems)

### Optional (for full functionality)
- `speedtest-cli` - For speed tests
- `dig` - For DNS timing (part of bind-utils/dnsutils)
- `mtr` - For route analysis

Install on Ubuntu/Debian:
```bash
sudo apt install speedtest-cli dnsutils mtr
```

Install on macOS:
```bash
brew install speedtest-cli mtr
```

## Optional Dependencies

Install specific feature sets:

```bash
pip install nettest[yaml]        # YAML configuration support
pip install nettest[prometheus]  # Prometheus metrics endpoint
pip install nettest[http]        # HTTP/webhook support
pip install nettest[full]        # All optional dependencies
```

